1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

2
00:00:23,645 --> 00:00:26,465
"Saeng Karun Foundation"

3
00:00:55,065 --> 00:00:59,025
Rise and shine, everyone.
The birds are already out.

4
00:00:59,425 --> 00:01:02,185
Get up.
Or Grandpa's coming to scold you.

5
00:01:22,945 --> 00:01:25,585
Make a fist and spin it round

6
00:01:25,615 --> 00:01:28,085
Raise your hands
and wave them side to side

7
00:01:28,105 --> 00:01:32,785
Spread your arms up and down,
fold and touch your shoulders

8
00:01:32,785 --> 00:01:35,105
Spread your arms up and down

9
00:01:35,105 --> 00:01:37,545
Stand up straight
and spin around

10
00:01:38,225 --> 00:01:40,225
Line up.

11
00:02:15,465 --> 00:02:16,625
Phi Oui, get me the eggs.

12
00:02:16,745 --> 00:02:18,175
(Phi, respectful honorific)

13
00:02:20,105 --> 00:02:21,105
Here.

14
00:02:23,865 --> 00:02:25,225
Now the zucchini, Phi Oui.

15
00:02:49,925 --> 00:02:52,425
Put it down, Mom.
Leave it to the young.

16
00:02:52,665 --> 00:02:54,785
Very well. You carry it over.

17
00:02:54,965 --> 00:02:57,225
Then come back and help Auntie Oui
lift the rice pot.

18
00:02:57,375 --> 00:02:58,545
Okay. Don't have to tell me.

19
00:02:59,185 --> 00:03:00,185
Hmph.

20
00:03:00,415 --> 00:03:02,665
- Hot stuff coming.
- Should I stop feeding you?

21
00:03:19,715 --> 00:03:21,145
Okay. Come on in.

22
00:03:22,525 --> 00:03:25,365
Here. Grab it. Okay.

23
00:03:25,385 --> 00:03:27,175
- Easy now.
- Yes.

24
00:03:27,195 --> 00:03:28,585
There we go. Okay.

25
00:03:30,005 --> 00:03:31,605
You're welcome. Here you go.

26
00:03:32,465 --> 00:03:34,305
- Alright, okay.
- Thank you.

27
00:03:34,435 --> 00:03:36,185
Give them plenty now.

28
00:03:36,185 --> 00:03:37,505
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

29
00:03:38,745 --> 00:03:42,785
Hey... hey, your pants.
Suck it in a little.

30
00:03:42,925 --> 00:03:43,925
There you go.

31
00:03:44,305 --> 00:03:46,805
Hmph...watch out
or they'll fall right off you.

32
00:03:47,665 --> 00:03:48,665
Nice job.

33
00:03:50,575 --> 00:03:52,745
Stop, stop. Pik, hold on.

34
00:03:54,875 --> 00:03:57,785
Here. Do not eat boogers, okay?

35
00:04:00,105 --> 00:04:01,825
Hey, not yet.

36
00:04:02,605 --> 00:04:05,185
Phi Pipe, leave me alone.

37
00:04:05,345 --> 00:04:07,435
Pipe, don't pick on her.

38
00:04:07,595 --> 00:04:09,265
Yes, Phi Save.

39
00:04:15,105 --> 00:04:17,185
Grandpa, go sit down.

40
00:04:17,525 --> 00:04:19,375
You could pass out
blowing that whistle.

41
00:04:19,465 --> 00:04:20,665
Stop before you drop.

42
00:04:20,945 --> 00:04:22,065
It's you who will drop.

43
00:04:22,065 --> 00:04:24,665
See? With this.

44
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:26,265
Go on.

45
00:04:26,465 --> 00:04:27,585
Stay with Mom, okay?

46
00:04:27,705 --> 00:04:28,705
Yeah.

47
00:04:29,615 --> 00:04:33,775
- One, two, three, four...
- Five, six, seven, eight.

48
00:04:33,945 --> 00:04:38,225
- One, two, three, four...
- Five, six, seven, eight.

49
00:04:38,415 --> 00:04:39,825
One...

50
00:04:40,485 --> 00:04:41,485
Hehe.

51
00:04:42,105 --> 00:04:45,065
Breakfast is ready. Stop playing.

52
00:04:46,385 --> 00:04:48,585
Just a little warm-up, Grandpa.

53
00:04:48,885 --> 00:04:50,615
So I can eat more.

54
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:53,705
Trying this move.
It's way more fun.

55
00:04:54,025 --> 00:04:56,695
People need to do things
one at a time.

56
00:04:57,395 --> 00:04:59,135
Take your seat.
We're about to eat.

57
00:04:59,745 --> 00:05:02,065
Kids these days always talk back.

58
00:05:03,305 --> 00:05:04,305
Go on.

59
00:05:12,125 --> 00:05:13,125
Mart.

60
00:05:13,875 --> 00:05:15,345
Any rice left?

61
00:05:15,445 --> 00:05:16,625
What's going on, Sorn?

62
00:05:16,985 --> 00:05:18,585
Someone dropped off a kid, Dad.

63
00:05:18,945 --> 00:05:20,545
She looks hungry.

64
00:06:10,185 --> 00:06:11,225
Thank you.

65
00:06:17,865 --> 00:06:19,025
Listen for the signal.

66
00:06:19,245 --> 00:06:21,885
Alright, let's eat.

67
00:06:21,925 --> 00:06:22,925
Yay.

68
00:06:39,195 --> 00:06:42,825
- Okay, hop on in. Careful now.
- Hurry, hurry.

69
00:06:45,365 --> 00:06:46,385
Serves you right.

70
00:06:47,225 --> 00:06:49,705
- Pipe.
- Pipe, at it again?

71
00:06:50,815 --> 00:06:54,425
Snow, hold it. Let him go.

72
00:06:58,755 --> 00:07:00,385
Dad, let's go.

73
00:07:01,345 --> 00:07:02,345
Okay.

74
00:07:04,065 --> 00:07:05,065
Bye-bye, Grandpa.

75
00:07:05,065 --> 00:07:07,185
- Bye-bye.
- Buh-bye.

76
00:07:09,945 --> 00:07:12,425
- Oh...
- That was fast.

77
00:07:22,755 --> 00:07:24,585
I already spoke
with the child's mother.

78
00:07:25,425 --> 00:07:27,385
Just three lanes down from here.

79
00:07:28,385 --> 00:07:29,385
No husband.

80
00:07:30,105 --> 00:07:32,865
Just lost her job.
She really can't manage.

81
00:07:41,535 --> 00:07:45,705
Girl, this place...
is your new home now.

82
00:07:46,295 --> 00:07:48,785
You'll have food to eat,
a place to sleep.

83
00:07:49,025 --> 00:07:50,505
Someone to look after you.

84
00:07:51,265 --> 00:07:52,945
You're safe now. Okay?

85
00:07:54,185 --> 00:07:55,705
Mm-hmm. Mart.

86
00:07:56,735 --> 00:07:58,735
Take her to see
where she'll be sleeping.

87
00:08:04,785 --> 00:08:06,825
Great. I'll show you.

88
00:08:14,995 --> 00:08:18,745
Dad, we can't take in
any more children.

89
00:08:18,965 --> 00:08:21,225
Why not? What's wrong?

90
00:08:31,035 --> 00:08:32,505
Hello.

91
00:08:32,865 --> 00:08:36,385
Good morning, Supaporn
calling from Thanarak Bank.

92
00:08:36,385 --> 00:08:39,185
May I speak
with Mr. Somsak Prasitphithaya?

93
00:08:39,465 --> 00:08:40,745
Speaking.

94
00:08:40,985 --> 00:08:42,985
The reason for my call today

95
00:08:43,015 --> 00:08:45,545
is that we have not received
a loan payment

96
00:08:45,545 --> 00:08:51,265
for December 2025
through January 2026.

97
00:08:51,545 --> 00:08:54,305
When would you be able
to make a payment, sir?

98
00:08:55,805 --> 00:08:57,005
Very soon.

99
00:09:11,145 --> 00:09:13,785
I'm dealing with
a few things right now.

100
00:09:13,935 --> 00:09:16,145
I must inform you of another matter.

101
00:09:16,145 --> 00:09:18,765
In February 2026,

102
00:09:18,785 --> 00:09:22,115
your reduced-rate agreement is
nearing the end of its grace period,

103
00:09:22,145 --> 00:09:25,565
after which your payments
will resume at the standard rate.

104
00:09:26,765 --> 00:09:28,785
And if I still can't pay?

105
00:09:29,345 --> 00:09:33,345
We encourage you to come in
for a consultation.

106
00:09:33,345 --> 00:09:36,625
Accounts over 180 days past due

107
00:09:36,775 --> 00:09:40,385
will be subject to legal action.

108
00:09:40,705 --> 00:09:42,305
I'm sorry... legal action?

109
00:09:43,945 --> 00:09:45,225
What happens then?

110
00:09:45,345 --> 00:09:46,365
Well...

111
00:09:46,855 --> 00:09:48,375
the Enforcement Department may

112
00:09:48,375 --> 00:09:50,265
seize the land used as collateral

113
00:09:50,265 --> 00:09:52,585
and sell it at auction
to settle the debt.

114
00:09:58,665 --> 00:10:00,585
How much do I still owe?

115
00:10:01,025 --> 00:10:02,425
Principal and interest

116
00:10:02,445 --> 00:10:07,285
comes to 12,508,649.75 baht.

117
00:10:08,985 --> 00:10:09,985
I see.

118
00:10:22,665 --> 00:10:25,545
Was that the bank?
What did they say?

119
00:10:25,805 --> 00:10:29,345
Hmm?
Nothing to worry yourself over.

120
00:10:31,065 --> 00:10:35,465
Over not making
loan payments on time?

121
00:10:36,545 --> 00:10:40,985
Dad, we barely can afford groceries
for the children.

122
00:10:41,265 --> 00:10:42,825
And then there's tuition
and everything else.

123
00:10:43,345 --> 00:10:46,305
Tonight they're delivering
rice and cooking gas,

124
00:10:46,605 --> 00:10:48,875
and I'm afraid
I have no money for those.

125
00:10:49,625 --> 00:10:52,865
It's all right. I'll sort it out.

126
00:10:53,185 --> 00:10:54,705
There's always a way.

127
00:10:59,305 --> 00:11:02,785
My elderly allowance just came in.
I'll transfer it over.

128
00:11:04,785 --> 00:11:05,785
How much is it?

129
00:11:05,885 --> 00:11:06,885
Seven hundred baht.

130
00:11:16,455 --> 00:11:19,465
Hey, Mom. Sitting out here again.

131
00:11:23,465 --> 00:11:25,585
Now listen.
I've told you many times,

132
00:11:25,585 --> 00:11:29,125
do not bring that out here.

133
00:11:29,395 --> 00:11:31,865
You could drop it.
Worth a lot, you know?

134
00:11:32,065 --> 00:11:34,705
Come on. Give it to me.

135
00:11:35,865 --> 00:11:38,265
Mm. It's getting hot out here.

136
00:11:38,785 --> 00:11:40,745
Better go sit inside. Come on.

137
00:11:41,145 --> 00:11:44,305
Come, come. Grab the cane.

138
00:11:44,715 --> 00:11:47,585
There we go. Up, up.
Can you make it?

139
00:11:47,935 --> 00:11:49,785
Alright, let's go.

140
00:11:50,095 --> 00:11:53,435
Easy steps. Go on. Go on.

141
00:11:56,755 --> 00:11:59,585
Alright, turn, turn.

142
00:12:00,265 --> 00:12:01,545
Now, back up.

143
00:12:02,755 --> 00:12:04,925
Back up. Easy, easy. There we go.

144
00:12:05,335 --> 00:12:08,705
Good. Very good.

145
00:12:20,675 --> 00:12:21,675
Huh.

146
00:12:22,035 --> 00:12:24,905
Mom, I'm heading up to work now.

147
00:13:07,985 --> 00:13:13,635
"Thailand Writers' Association,
Certificate, Somsak Prasitpittaya"

148
00:13:24,355 --> 00:13:26,695
"Saming the Slayer, Volume 2"

149
00:13:32,435 --> 00:13:35,225
"Saming the Slayer 2,
by Harn Chanprai"

150
00:13:47,525 --> 00:13:48,525
Hmph.

151
00:13:51,615 --> 00:13:52,615
Go, go.

152
00:13:53,145 --> 00:13:54,185
Hey, hey. Watch it.

153
00:14:08,805 --> 00:14:09,805
Hey.

154
00:14:11,005 --> 00:14:12,205
Pheem. Pheem.

155
00:14:13,045 --> 00:14:14,105
Hey, block it. Block.

156
00:14:14,985 --> 00:14:17,545
- Yeah...
- Yeah...

157
00:14:18,865 --> 00:14:20,305
- Yeah.
- What the.

158
00:14:21,265 --> 00:14:23,825
Hey, hey. Why aren't you in class?

159
00:14:24,525 --> 00:14:25,985
Get to class. Now.

160
00:14:29,865 --> 00:14:32,345
Tuck in your shirt too.

161
00:14:33,355 --> 00:14:34,625
You...

162
00:14:35,545 --> 00:14:36,545
Hey.

163
00:14:37,625 --> 00:14:38,625
Supawit.

164
00:14:40,065 --> 00:14:41,195
You're on a scholarship.

165
00:14:41,195 --> 00:14:44,225
Why not show your friends how to be
studious and not skip class?

166
00:14:44,825 --> 00:14:46,705
Go before they pull
your scholarship.

167
00:14:46,785 --> 00:14:50,425
Too late for that, teacher.
It's my last semester.

168
00:14:51,145 --> 00:14:53,745
And I already got into uni.
So why must I go to class?

169
00:14:53,745 --> 00:14:56,105
If you're at school,
you go to class.

170
00:14:56,615 --> 00:14:58,965
And this is no time
for soccer, right?

171
00:14:59,605 --> 00:15:02,265
Besides, you two

172
00:15:02,265 --> 00:15:04,745
still have final exams
just like everyone else.

173
00:15:05,225 --> 00:15:09,305
Please, just this one period.
Cut us some slack.

174
00:15:09,305 --> 00:15:12,145
Even if I go,
I won't pay attention anyway.

175
00:15:12,585 --> 00:15:13,625
I'll just bother everyone.

176
00:15:13,865 --> 00:15:15,385
You two wear me out.

177
00:15:15,695 --> 00:15:19,615
Fine. But no soccer.
The other kids can see you.

178
00:15:19,905 --> 00:15:21,265
Hang out somewhere else.

179
00:15:21,545 --> 00:15:23,545
- Yes.
- Got it.

180
00:15:23,545 --> 00:15:24,545
Okay.

181
00:15:25,955 --> 00:15:27,345
Hey, all of you go to class.

182
00:15:28,175 --> 00:15:30,185
Lucky for us,
Kru (teacher) Met came.

183
00:15:30,515 --> 00:15:32,785
Kru Suri could've dragged us
to her office.

184
00:15:32,975 --> 00:15:35,265
Well, let's bounce
before she gets here.

185
00:15:35,745 --> 00:15:36,745
Yeah?

186
00:15:41,105 --> 00:15:42,105
Ugh.

187
00:15:42,855 --> 00:15:43,905
You think you got me?

188
00:16:22,405 --> 00:16:25,785
Hey Guy, all your posts are
in Close Friends, huh?

189
00:16:26,625 --> 00:16:27,705
Who else is in there?

190
00:16:27,705 --> 00:16:28,705
Just you.

191
00:16:31,835 --> 00:16:32,835
And some others.

192
00:16:35,945 --> 00:16:36,945
Who?

193
00:16:38,905 --> 00:16:39,905
Secret?

194
00:16:40,425 --> 00:16:41,335
No.

195
00:16:41,405 --> 00:16:42,405
Hmm?

196
00:16:43,275 --> 00:16:44,375
Not telling me?

197
00:16:47,185 --> 00:16:49,265
Will we still be friends
after we graduate?

198
00:16:49,985 --> 00:16:50,985
Why?

199
00:16:51,035 --> 00:16:54,825
Well...we'll be at different unis.
So far apart.

200
00:16:55,025 --> 00:16:56,385
We won't see each other much.

201
00:16:59,675 --> 00:17:00,745
Come on.

202
00:17:01,365 --> 00:17:04,325
You'll make new friends in no time
and forget all about me.

203
00:17:04,825 --> 00:17:09,345
An athlete like you,
I bet you'll have a girl in a week.

204
00:17:16,825 --> 00:17:17,825
Hey, Save.

205
00:17:19,495 --> 00:17:20,495
Yeah?

206
00:17:21,345 --> 00:17:22,545
I just want to tell you...

207
00:17:25,475 --> 00:17:26,475
Hmm?

208
00:17:28,185 --> 00:17:29,425
Tell me what? Just say it.

209
00:17:33,265 --> 00:17:34,745
We'll still be friends.

210
00:17:35,745 --> 00:17:37,855
I'll make sure we hang out
all the time. Okay?

211
00:17:39,785 --> 00:17:42,385
Of course. What's gotten into you?

212
00:17:43,215 --> 00:17:44,555
Stuttering and spacing out.

213
00:17:45,465 --> 00:17:47,295
I didn't want to
say something cheesy.

214
00:17:48,585 --> 00:17:51,985
Go ahead and say it. I won't gag.

215
00:17:53,705 --> 00:17:56,265
What's wrong with you?
You're being weird.

216
00:18:06,455 --> 00:18:07,455
Mm.

217
00:18:09,545 --> 00:18:11,245
- Phi Sorn.
- Hmm?

218
00:18:11,265 --> 00:18:12,545
Is this ride far from here?

219
00:18:13,505 --> 00:18:14,945
Not at all. Just two lanes over.

220
00:18:15,105 --> 00:18:16,105
Good.

221
00:18:16,205 --> 00:18:19,395
Don't take another job yet.
I have a new project.

222
00:18:20,065 --> 00:18:21,065
What project?

223
00:18:21,095 --> 00:18:23,465
Mm. Just finish the job and return.

224
00:18:23,605 --> 00:18:24,605
Mm-hmm.

225
00:18:33,155 --> 00:18:34,155
Be careful.

226
00:18:42,565 --> 00:18:46,105
Phi Sorn, shouldn't we get
a handyman for this?

227
00:18:46,505 --> 00:18:49,905
We've got everything we need.
Why waste money?

228
00:18:50,665 --> 00:18:52,345
You actually know what you're doing?

229
00:18:53,335 --> 00:18:54,535
Trust me.

230
00:18:56,105 --> 00:18:59,305
Just need to check the drill first.
Been sitting a while.

231
00:18:59,785 --> 00:19:01,025
It may be rusted.

232
00:19:02,085 --> 00:19:03,085
Here.

233
00:19:06,075 --> 00:19:08,785
Take this. Wait right here.

234
00:19:25,705 --> 00:19:26,865
Oh, Grandma.

235
00:19:27,825 --> 00:19:29,385
Just watching us work?

236
00:19:29,985 --> 00:19:31,865
You just sit and watch;
no need to help.

237
00:19:31,995 --> 00:19:34,825
- We've got this.
- Oh no, Grandma.

238
00:19:35,075 --> 00:19:38,365
Just cheer us on from here.
That's plenty.

239
00:19:39,275 --> 00:19:43,555
And why are you holding that clock?
It's worth a lot, you know?

240
00:20:16,425 --> 00:20:17,425
Ugh.

241
00:20:23,605 --> 00:20:26,425
- Easy now.
- Good.

242
00:20:27,445 --> 00:20:30,265
What are you two doing?

243
00:20:31,005 --> 00:20:32,005
What is it, Dad?

244
00:20:34,245 --> 00:20:36,185
Ugh.

245
00:20:46,105 --> 00:20:48,025
Watch the hand. Be careful.

246
00:20:48,055 --> 00:20:49,675
Yeah, I know what I'm doing.

247
00:20:50,465 --> 00:20:51,945
You sure about that?

248
00:20:51,975 --> 00:20:53,065
Absolutely.

249
00:21:02,945 --> 00:21:04,745
Hey, anybody kicked the plug?

250
00:21:04,975 --> 00:21:05,975
I did.

251
00:21:06,195 --> 00:21:07,195
Oof.

252
00:21:08,105 --> 00:21:11,265
What's all the racket?
It drove me mad upstairs.

253
00:21:11,985 --> 00:21:16,305
Phi Sorn is making a trellis
for the vegetable garden.

254
00:21:16,475 --> 00:21:18,545
A trellis? What for?

255
00:21:18,775 --> 00:21:20,025
Well, it's obvious.

256
00:21:20,305 --> 00:21:23,345
So we can save money on buying them.

257
00:21:23,595 --> 00:21:26,085
Oh? Is that so?

258
00:21:26,105 --> 00:21:26,875
Mm-hmm.

259
00:21:26,985 --> 00:21:28,225
You all know how to do that?

260
00:21:28,225 --> 00:21:29,865
Can't be that hard.

261
00:21:29,865 --> 00:21:33,385
Drop some seeds, water them,
wait for them to grow.

262
00:21:33,385 --> 00:21:35,225
Then pick and eat. Simple as that.

263
00:21:35,765 --> 00:21:36,765
Mm.

264
00:21:37,345 --> 00:21:40,545
Alright. Just keep it down a little.

265
00:21:41,095 --> 00:21:42,505
It's bothering me.

266
00:21:42,685 --> 00:21:43,785
Yes.

267
00:21:51,785 --> 00:21:52,905
Sorry, Father.

268
00:21:56,325 --> 00:21:57,425
We should hurry.

269
00:22:00,385 --> 00:22:04,025
Oh, Mom. Not again.

270
00:22:06,545 --> 00:22:09,585
What is it with you and that clock?

271
00:22:11,735 --> 00:22:12,945
Give me that.

272
00:22:22,095 --> 00:22:23,095
Hmph.

273
00:22:25,285 --> 00:22:27,985
Keep doing that,
and you'll pull something.

274
00:22:55,105 --> 00:22:56,185
You heading straight home?

275
00:22:56,465 --> 00:22:57,465
Yeah.

276
00:22:57,625 --> 00:23:00,145
My mom just messaged me
to help Dad with something.

277
00:23:00,905 --> 00:23:02,585
Okay. I'm heading home.

278
00:23:03,265 --> 00:23:04,265
Let's go.

279
00:23:18,225 --> 00:23:19,225
Hey, Save.

280
00:23:19,735 --> 00:23:20,735
Yeah?

281
00:23:23,625 --> 00:23:26,505
If I tell you something,
can you promise you won't hate me?

282
00:23:27,575 --> 00:23:28,665
What is it? Just say it.

283
00:23:29,065 --> 00:23:31,065
Well, I...

284
00:23:33,025 --> 00:23:34,735
- I like...
- I'm waiting out front.

285
00:23:37,565 --> 00:23:38,965
Who were you just talking to?

286
00:23:39,205 --> 00:23:41,715
It's Jang, asking me to go to Siam.

287
00:23:41,985 --> 00:23:44,385
What about...
going home to help your dad?

288
00:23:44,385 --> 00:23:46,965
Oh, that can wait.
Scoping out girls comes first.

289
00:23:48,265 --> 00:23:49,745
So...you were saying?

290
00:23:51,245 --> 00:23:52,705
Nothing. Forget it.

291
00:23:53,465 --> 00:23:54,625
Hey.

292
00:23:55,985 --> 00:23:57,265
What is it? Tell me.

293
00:23:59,955 --> 00:24:00,955
It's just...

294
00:24:02,285 --> 00:24:03,945
I was going to say I...

295
00:24:06,905 --> 00:24:07,905
like...

296
00:24:07,935 --> 00:24:09,105
Hey, Save.

297
00:24:10,805 --> 00:24:11,805
Ow.

298
00:24:12,065 --> 00:24:13,065
Hey, you okay?

299
00:24:13,445 --> 00:24:14,465
Ow, that hurt.

300
00:24:14,495 --> 00:24:16,665
That's nothing. You're so dramatic.

301
00:24:19,615 --> 00:24:21,185
Guy, you coming with us or not?

302
00:24:21,425 --> 00:24:22,465
- You in?
- Yeah, I'm in.

303
00:24:22,975 --> 00:24:26,655
Well, it's a mess, really.
I still don't know what to do.

304
00:24:28,835 --> 00:24:31,465
Thank you, honestly.
Thank you so much.

305
00:24:32,215 --> 00:24:33,745
I really appreciate it.

306
00:24:34,305 --> 00:24:37,505
I won't forget this.
I really mean it.

307
00:24:53,055 --> 00:24:54,055
Hey.

308
00:24:54,505 --> 00:24:56,905
Mom, where's the clock?

309
00:24:59,865 --> 00:25:02,025
The one you always carry around.
Where is it?

310
00:25:11,245 --> 00:25:12,245
Where did you put it?

311
00:25:16,585 --> 00:25:18,785
It's gone. Where did you leave it?

312
00:25:19,225 --> 00:25:20,705
What are you looking for?

313
00:25:20,775 --> 00:25:23,585
The clock that was always up there.

314
00:25:24,045 --> 00:25:25,985
Oh, I haven't seen it at all.

315
00:25:26,265 --> 00:25:28,145
No idea where Mom left it.

316
00:25:28,745 --> 00:25:31,385
That clock isn't any regular one.

317
00:25:31,705 --> 00:25:36,425
The former Army Commander gave it
to me as a wedding gift.

318
00:25:38,435 --> 00:25:40,305
Who were you on the phone with
just now?

319
00:25:40,635 --> 00:25:41,945
Me, on the phone?

320
00:25:42,215 --> 00:25:44,865
Yeah, you. I saw you on the phone.

321
00:25:45,465 --> 00:25:46,785
Oh...

322
00:25:47,395 --> 00:25:49,305
Um, I was talking to...

323
00:25:50,985 --> 00:25:52,305
- A friend.
- A friend?

324
00:25:52,615 --> 00:25:54,655
An old friend.
Hadn't spoken to in a while.

325
00:25:54,695 --> 00:25:56,895
Mm-hmm. So it took you
a while to answer me?

326
00:25:57,455 --> 00:25:58,325
Hehe.

327
00:25:58,345 --> 00:26:00,545
My, so forgetful at your age.

328
00:26:00,605 --> 00:26:05,025
You'll be like my mom soon, huh?

329
00:26:05,465 --> 00:26:08,985
And if you find that clock,
put it back where it belongs.

330
00:26:09,515 --> 00:26:10,705
Yes, Father.

331
00:26:10,725 --> 00:26:11,725
Right.

332
00:26:12,065 --> 00:26:14,705
Mom, this can't keep happening.

333
00:26:15,905 --> 00:26:17,305
Things keep going missing.

334
00:26:18,225 --> 00:26:19,585
I can't keep up with this.

335
00:26:24,725 --> 00:26:25,785
Let's kick some ball.

336
00:26:31,935 --> 00:26:33,105
We're here already.

337
00:26:35,185 --> 00:26:39,185
Alright, engine's off.
Everyone can get out now.

338
00:26:40,015 --> 00:26:42,365
- Thank you.
- Yes, yes. Don't run. You'll fall.

339
00:26:42,385 --> 00:26:44,985
- Thank you.
- Go on, kids. Watch yourself.

340
00:26:44,985 --> 00:26:46,345
- Easy, easy.
- Thank you.

341
00:26:46,375 --> 00:26:48,585
Oh, oh. Careful. Here.

342
00:26:48,845 --> 00:26:51,785
Slow down
or you'll trip over yourself.

343
00:26:51,785 --> 00:26:54,905
Good girl.
Go wash up and do your homework.

344
00:26:54,935 --> 00:26:55,985
Alright, that's everyone.

345
00:26:55,985 --> 00:26:56,985
Ugh.

346
00:26:57,695 --> 00:26:59,265
Pipe, you...

347
00:27:05,825 --> 00:27:07,105
Hey, hey. Guys.

348
00:27:26,435 --> 00:27:27,545
I'm Snow.

349
00:27:27,545 --> 00:27:28,625
I'm Mabel.

350
00:27:28,625 --> 00:27:31,985
I'm Yoyo. What's your name?

351
00:27:32,185 --> 00:27:33,985
My name is Jingjai.

352
00:27:36,945 --> 00:27:39,665
Jingjai, Auntie Oui asked us
to look after you.

353
00:27:39,905 --> 00:27:41,785
Come on, we'll give you
the home tour.

354
00:27:42,345 --> 00:27:44,105
She already did.

355
00:27:46,305 --> 00:27:48,025
But there are rules
you need to know.

356
00:27:48,305 --> 00:27:51,585
I'm sure she didn't tell you.

357
00:27:55,425 --> 00:28:01,105
Bathroom rules.
Two minutes per person. That's it.

358
00:28:01,105 --> 00:28:02,825
What? Only two minutes?

359
00:28:02,955 --> 00:28:03,955
Yes.

360
00:28:04,005 --> 00:28:10,105
If you go over, you're scrubbing
smelly toilets for a week.

361
00:28:11,305 --> 00:28:13,345
It's not personal.
It just wastes water.

362
00:28:14,465 --> 00:28:16,385
Right. Two minutes, no more.

363
00:28:20,475 --> 00:28:21,895
This is the dining area.

364
00:28:21,925 --> 00:28:25,205
We all come together
for every meal, every day.

365
00:28:25,665 --> 00:28:26,945
Mealtime rules.

366
00:28:26,945 --> 00:28:29,545
Finish everything on your plate.
Not a single grain left.

367
00:28:29,545 --> 00:28:30,905
No food waste.

368
00:28:31,145 --> 00:28:33,025
Trying to sneak it out?

369
00:28:33,045 --> 00:28:35,275
You get no meal for a week.

370
00:28:35,865 --> 00:28:37,545
That could starve someone to death.

371
00:28:39,095 --> 00:28:41,855
We all have to be frugal.
No throwing food away.

372
00:28:42,425 --> 00:28:45,065
Every plate, every dish.

373
00:28:45,085 --> 00:28:48,165
Nothing goes to waste.
Food is precious.

374
00:28:50,145 --> 00:28:51,705
And this is the computer room.

375
00:28:52,025 --> 00:28:54,185
For homework and studying.

376
00:28:54,375 --> 00:28:58,185
If you want to use a computer,
sign in right there.

377
00:29:00,695 --> 00:29:02,705
But no more than thirty minutes.

378
00:29:03,065 --> 00:29:07,305
If you go over,
no social media for you. Forever.

379
00:29:07,825 --> 00:29:09,825
Don't linger.
It runs up the electric bill.

380
00:29:19,745 --> 00:29:21,745
Last stop: the bedroom.

381
00:29:22,025 --> 00:29:24,425
Everyone lights out at nine.

382
00:29:24,865 --> 00:29:26,865
If anyone refuses to sleep...

383
00:29:28,665 --> 00:29:30,125
- The ghost will get you.
- The ghost will get you.

384
00:29:40,085 --> 00:29:43,025
Hey, the power's out.

385
00:29:44,185 --> 00:29:46,145
Get a flashlight.
I'll check on the kids.

386
00:29:46,355 --> 00:29:47,465
Hm...

387
00:29:48,665 --> 00:29:52,065
The electric authority
said nothing about a blackout.

388
00:29:52,865 --> 00:29:54,345
Oh, now I remember.

389
00:29:54,875 --> 00:29:56,825
- Remember what?
- I forgot to pay the bill.

390
00:29:56,855 --> 00:30:00,255
Sorn, it's important. How could you?

391
00:30:00,545 --> 00:30:04,025
Well, Mart borrowed it that day to
get school uniforms for the kids.

392
00:30:04,025 --> 00:30:06,825
She hasn't paid me back,
so it slipped my mind.

393
00:30:07,145 --> 00:30:10,625
Don't blame me.
I just need more time.

394
00:30:10,685 --> 00:30:13,905
And you never reminded me.
I figured paid it after all.

395
00:30:13,905 --> 00:30:15,865
Why did you assume?

396
00:30:15,945 --> 00:30:20,305
I've got a lot to do:
deliveries, errands, on and on.

397
00:30:20,305 --> 00:30:23,745
Of course, things slip my mind.
The borrower should follow up.

398
00:30:23,745 --> 00:30:25,945
Ow, I'm busy too.

399
00:30:25,945 --> 00:30:28,465
My head's spinning all the time.

400
00:30:28,465 --> 00:30:30,905
Alright, alright. That's enough.

401
00:30:31,395 --> 00:30:32,785
Go pay it tomorrow.

402
00:30:33,585 --> 00:30:35,545
Flashlight.
I'm gonna check on the kids.

403
00:30:36,735 --> 00:30:37,735
Oh.

404
00:30:38,595 --> 00:30:39,595
Yeah?

405
00:30:41,095 --> 00:30:42,825
Uh. What's going on?

406
00:30:42,965 --> 00:30:45,225
Dead batteries.
Haven't used it in ages.

407
00:30:45,505 --> 00:30:48,465
What actually works in this house?

408
00:30:50,425 --> 00:30:53,425
Happy birthday to you.

409
00:30:53,455 --> 00:30:54,505
Whose birthday is it?

410
00:30:54,535 --> 00:30:57,705
Haha. Don't mess around.
The power's out.

411
00:30:58,245 --> 00:31:00,265
Your dad forgot to pay the bill.

412
00:31:00,545 --> 00:31:02,105
Your mom borrowed the money.

413
00:31:02,465 --> 00:31:05,105
Alright, enough. It's fine.

414
00:31:05,665 --> 00:31:07,945
Save, go check on the kids.

415
00:31:08,345 --> 00:31:09,065
Yes.

416
00:31:09,265 --> 00:31:11,025
Oh, and fetch Auntie Oui for me.

417
00:31:11,295 --> 00:31:12,295
Got it.

418
00:31:14,395 --> 00:31:17,625
And... where's the cake
and candles, Grandpa?

419
00:31:18,115 --> 00:31:18,825
Hmm?

420
00:31:18,955 --> 00:31:20,225
Cake and candles?

421
00:31:21,365 --> 00:31:24,445
Go now, or I'll push you there
with my foot.

422
00:31:24,465 --> 00:31:25,505
Oh, I'd better hurry.

423
00:31:25,975 --> 00:31:27,945
- Hurry with my foot?
- I'm going, I'm going.

424
00:31:40,135 --> 00:31:41,445
- Auntie Oui.
- Yes.

425
00:31:41,475 --> 00:31:42,475
Mom needs you.

426
00:31:42,495 --> 00:31:45,655
Oh, alright.
You keep an eye on the kids.

427
00:31:46,125 --> 00:31:47,345
Just watch them. That's it?

428
00:31:47,455 --> 00:31:49,105
Whatever you say, Save.

429
00:31:51,385 --> 00:31:52,385
This way.

430
00:31:59,015 --> 00:32:01,185
Phi (honorific) Save, I'm scared.

431
00:32:01,425 --> 00:32:04,665
Why? You sleep with the lights off
every night.

432
00:32:06,705 --> 00:32:07,215
Hmm?

433
00:32:07,625 --> 00:32:11,665
But it's a blackout.
Is the house ghost messing with us?

434
00:32:12,385 --> 00:32:15,345
You mean Tiad?
He should've reincarnated ages ago.

435
00:32:15,985 --> 00:32:16,985
Look...

436
00:32:17,545 --> 00:32:19,105
Hey, Snow.

437
00:32:20,065 --> 00:32:23,125
Hmm? You made up
a scary tale again?

438
00:32:23,295 --> 00:32:27,185
I did not. I did see him
in a photo smiling.

439
00:32:27,665 --> 00:32:28,785
You were paranoid.

440
00:32:29,225 --> 00:32:31,625
- I wasn't.
- Hey, guys.

441
00:32:32,265 --> 00:32:33,885
How about something fun?

442
00:32:33,915 --> 00:32:35,915
Good idea, good idea.

443
00:32:35,965 --> 00:32:38,865
Quick. Gather round. Come close.

444
00:33:16,345 --> 00:33:18,465
And the final transformation.

445
00:33:19,185 --> 00:33:20,465
A werewolf.

446
00:33:20,865 --> 00:33:31,145
Wrruff!

447
00:33:39,955 --> 00:33:41,985
Save, come here a second.

448
00:33:42,005 --> 00:33:43,005
Coming.

449
00:33:43,315 --> 00:33:44,785
Snow, my phone please.

450
00:33:45,545 --> 00:33:47,905
- I'll be right back, yeah?
- Phi Save, keep dancing.

451
00:33:47,905 --> 00:33:50,145
Hey, I'll be back.
You guys stay put.

452
00:33:50,185 --> 00:33:52,305
Okay?. Be right back.

453
00:33:52,335 --> 00:33:53,625
- Phi Save...
- I'll come back.

454
00:33:53,825 --> 00:33:55,825
Why? It's scary.

455
00:33:55,995 --> 00:33:57,705
That was terrifying.

456
00:33:57,735 --> 00:34:00,865
Mom always breaks up the fun.

457
00:34:01,355 --> 00:34:03,365
- Did you hurt bad?
- Ow.

458
00:34:03,365 --> 00:34:04,705
Reached up and my back went out.

459
00:34:04,705 --> 00:34:05,865
Oh, no.

460
00:34:06,745 --> 00:34:07,585
Yeah, Mom?

461
00:34:07,585 --> 00:34:10,585
Your dad just threw out his back
reaching up there.

462
00:34:10,865 --> 00:34:12,905
There. Get that box from up top.

463
00:34:13,025 --> 00:34:14,025
What do you need, Mom?

464
00:34:14,395 --> 00:34:16,385
A lantern for the kids.

465
00:34:16,385 --> 00:34:19,345
Don't want to use candles.
Something might catch fire.

466
00:34:19,585 --> 00:34:21,545
We should use electric lanterns.

467
00:34:21,825 --> 00:34:24,265
Nobody uses oil lanterns anymore.

468
00:34:24,735 --> 00:34:28,385
Right there is a brain.
Wonder where he gets that from.

469
00:34:29,255 --> 00:34:30,665
- Come on.
- Where?

470
00:34:31,165 --> 00:34:32,445
- There.
- Here?

471
00:34:32,475 --> 00:34:34,265
- Careful, it's high.
- Easy, easy.

472
00:34:34,265 --> 00:34:35,945
- Watch out.
- Dad, a little push.

473
00:34:37,335 --> 00:34:39,755
- Push him.
- Ow, hold on. Ugh.

474
00:34:39,775 --> 00:34:43,955
Support him. Easy now.
Watch that stuff on top.

475
00:34:45,765 --> 00:34:48,675
He's taking too long.
It's been forever.

476
00:34:49,825 --> 00:34:51,625
Mom and Dad definitely
put him to work.

477
00:34:52,135 --> 00:34:53,135
Mm.

478
00:35:03,285 --> 00:35:04,665
Hey, Pipe.

479
00:35:04,665 --> 00:35:05,985
Shh.

480
00:35:08,625 --> 00:35:10,865
Awoo.

481
00:35:11,665 --> 00:35:15,825
- Awoo.
- Awoo.

482
00:35:16,005 --> 00:35:17,055
Look.

483
00:35:17,105 --> 00:35:19,865
Awoo.

484
00:35:21,025 --> 00:35:22,185
Not even close.

485
00:35:22,505 --> 00:35:25,945
Well, you think you can do better?

486
00:35:31,945 --> 00:35:34,505
Awoo...woo.

487
00:35:35,225 --> 00:35:37,505
- Awoo...
- Awoo...

488
00:35:39,455 --> 00:35:42,225
Werewolf or mangy mutt.

489
00:35:42,505 --> 00:35:47,385
- Mangy mutt.
- Mangy mutt.

490
00:35:48,155 --> 00:35:49,155
Hey.

491
00:36:04,335 --> 00:36:04,905
Ow.

492
00:36:04,935 --> 00:36:06,105
- Hey.
- Hey.

493
00:36:11,615 --> 00:36:13,985
Pipe, look what you did.

494
00:36:14,305 --> 00:36:15,745
You knocked me first.

495
00:36:16,025 --> 00:36:17,265
You pushed me first.

496
00:36:17,825 --> 00:36:19,225
Because you shoved me.

497
00:36:19,225 --> 00:36:20,185
I did not.

498
00:36:20,185 --> 00:36:21,945
Let's ask them.
They saw the whole thing.

499
00:36:29,075 --> 00:36:31,105
Fire. Fire.

500
00:36:33,845 --> 00:36:35,425
Hey. Fire.

501
00:36:37,405 --> 00:36:39,605
- Hey.
- Hey, fire.

502
00:36:41,175 --> 00:36:42,265
Fire.

503
00:36:42,545 --> 00:36:43,825
- What?
- What?

504
00:36:44,365 --> 00:36:46,465
- Hey.
- Go look.

505
00:36:50,925 --> 00:36:52,365
Everyone, get down.

506
00:36:57,825 --> 00:36:59,505
Everyone, crawl to the door.

507
00:37:01,105 --> 00:37:02,745
Dad, spray it. Spray it.

508
00:37:03,585 --> 00:37:05,185
What's wrong, Dad?

509
00:37:05,335 --> 00:37:06,785
I don't know. Something's wrong.

510
00:37:06,785 --> 00:37:08,425
Is it expired? Come on.

511
00:37:08,425 --> 00:37:09,425
We're done for.

512
00:37:09,865 --> 00:37:12,485
Ow. Everyone, follow me.

513
00:37:13,145 --> 00:37:14,345
Snow, why are you crawling?

514
00:37:15,185 --> 00:37:17,145
To get under the smoke.
Everyone get down.

515
00:37:18,085 --> 00:37:19,465
There's hardly any smoke.

516
00:37:19,465 --> 00:37:22,065
- Get up. Get out now.
- Get up.

517
00:37:22,065 --> 00:37:24,545
Out, out, out. Quick.

518
00:37:25,065 --> 00:37:26,145
Children, this way.

519
00:37:26,165 --> 00:37:27,545
Go on, hurry along.

520
00:37:27,565 --> 00:37:29,165
Be careful.

521
00:37:29,185 --> 00:37:30,395
- You got it?
- Whoa.

522
00:37:30,875 --> 00:37:31,905
Hey.

523
00:37:35,265 --> 00:37:36,705
Sorn, why aren't you spraying it?

524
00:37:36,845 --> 00:37:38,065
It won't come out.

525
00:37:38,925 --> 00:37:39,925
Whoa.

526
00:37:40,455 --> 00:37:41,705
Hack. Hack.

527
00:37:42,115 --> 00:37:43,115
Oh no.

528
00:37:47,555 --> 00:37:48,865
Ah, let's go.

529
00:37:50,735 --> 00:37:51,735
Hurry, hurry.

530
00:37:59,915 --> 00:38:00,705
Mom.

531
00:38:00,725 --> 00:38:01,565
- Hey.
- What?

532
00:38:01,585 --> 00:38:02,745
Good grief.

533
00:38:03,245 --> 00:38:04,785
Aw.

534
00:38:05,915 --> 00:38:07,265
Great-grandma,
how did you get here?

535
00:38:07,265 --> 00:38:09,345
Her timing couldn't be worse.

536
00:38:11,265 --> 00:38:13,425
Dad, don't. I'll handle it.

537
00:38:13,425 --> 00:38:14,945
Take her outside.

538
00:38:14,975 --> 00:38:15,975
Quickly.

539
00:38:15,985 --> 00:38:17,105
Save, go get more buckets.

540
00:38:17,585 --> 00:38:19,225
- Hurry. Give me that.
- Okay.

541
00:38:19,565 --> 00:38:20,585
- Here.
- Yes.

542
00:38:21,685 --> 00:38:23,065
- Water.
- Get Grandma out, Dad.

543
00:38:24,395 --> 00:38:25,755
Mom, let's go.

544
00:38:27,875 --> 00:38:30,285
- Please calm down.
- Ugh.

545
00:38:30,305 --> 00:38:31,585
Mom, stop fighting.

546
00:38:36,425 --> 00:38:37,945
- Get out now.
- Hurry.

547
00:38:44,745 --> 00:38:47,385
Is our house going to be okay?

548
00:38:47,645 --> 00:38:49,365
The whole place is gonna burn.

549
00:38:49,485 --> 00:38:52,505
And it'll spread to the neighbors.

550
00:38:53,305 --> 00:38:56,385
Stink breath.
That's not gonna happen.

551
00:38:56,905 --> 00:39:00,225
It is burning.
All because of you, Pipe.

552
00:39:01,785 --> 00:39:04,945
Yeah, you started it. Put it out.

553
00:39:04,945 --> 00:39:06,985
Enough.
Everyone, follow me.

554
00:39:08,405 --> 00:39:09,405
Ow.

555
00:39:11,225 --> 00:39:12,465
How could it be broken?

556
00:39:12,495 --> 00:39:17,145
I still haven't found a husband.
I'm not ready to die.

557
00:39:17,435 --> 00:39:19,785
Water's here.
Mom, water.

558
00:39:19,805 --> 00:39:20,475
Water's here.

559
00:39:20,505 --> 00:39:21,505
Here, here.

560
00:39:22,075 --> 00:39:23,945
Water's here.

561
00:39:24,345 --> 00:39:26,065
Save, get more water.

562
00:39:26,095 --> 00:39:27,095
Okay.

563
00:39:27,115 --> 00:39:29,785
- We're here to help.
- Help is here.

564
00:39:54,025 --> 00:40:01,645
- Yeah...
- Yeah...

565
00:40:01,645 --> 00:40:03,265
We did it.

566
00:40:03,395 --> 00:40:05,345
We don't have to
sleep on the street after all.

567
00:40:05,795 --> 00:40:06,795
Oh.

568
00:40:07,505 --> 00:40:08,745
Why did you say that, Mabel?

569
00:40:09,525 --> 00:40:13,425
Because without this house,
we'd have nowhere to go.

570
00:40:22,985 --> 00:40:23,985
Huh.

571
00:40:26,065 --> 00:40:28,445
Save's helping Auntie Oui
clean up now.

572
00:40:28,745 --> 00:40:30,855
Tonight the kids should
be able to sleep inside.

573
00:40:30,875 --> 00:40:31,875
Mm.

574
00:40:33,225 --> 00:40:36,065
Phi Sorn, pay the electric bill
right now.

575
00:40:36,345 --> 00:40:39,625
I looked it up for our area.

576
00:40:39,625 --> 00:40:42,545
If we pay now,
they can still come out tonight.

577
00:40:42,575 --> 00:40:44,145
We'll have power back right away.

578
00:40:44,545 --> 00:40:45,545
- Really?
- Mm.

579
00:40:46,325 --> 00:40:49,975
And we should get new bedding
and a new fire extinguisher.

580
00:40:50,235 --> 00:40:52,465
Alright. I'll pull money
from the bank.

581
00:40:53,145 --> 00:40:56,665
I'm afraid it's not enough
for the power bill.

582
00:40:57,025 --> 00:40:59,185
Then I'll find a way.

583
00:40:59,775 --> 00:41:03,335
Dad, I know you love this place.

584
00:41:03,665 --> 00:41:05,065
I do too.

585
00:41:05,825 --> 00:41:08,185
But we're getting
stretched too thin.

586
00:41:08,185 --> 00:41:10,185
I'm working on it.

587
00:41:14,545 --> 00:41:15,545
Father.

588
00:41:16,125 --> 00:41:17,545
The clock on the shelf.

589
00:41:18,545 --> 00:41:20,225
Grandma didn't take it anywhere.

590
00:41:21,145 --> 00:41:22,225
I did.

591
00:41:23,625 --> 00:41:26,715
I've been quietly pawning off
old things from the house.

592
00:41:27,075 --> 00:41:28,335
Quite a few pieces by now.

593
00:41:29,265 --> 00:41:30,895
What? No wonder.

594
00:41:31,475 --> 00:41:33,985
The place has been looking emptier.

595
00:41:34,605 --> 00:41:37,655
Mart, why didn't you
talk to us first?

596
00:41:38,175 --> 00:41:40,625
Well, if I'd told you that,

597
00:41:40,625 --> 00:41:42,095
would you have let me?

598
00:41:42,115 --> 00:41:44,545
There might have been another way.

599
00:41:44,905 --> 00:41:46,745
There wasn't another way.

600
00:41:47,615 --> 00:41:49,765
Otherwise, we wouldn't be
stressed out like this.

601
00:41:53,625 --> 00:41:57,025
I'm sorry, Father.
But I really had no choice.

602
00:41:59,255 --> 00:42:02,105
Dad, don't be angry with Mart.

603
00:42:02,585 --> 00:42:04,905
I'll find the money
to get everything out of pawn.

604
00:42:05,865 --> 00:42:06,865
No need.

605
00:42:07,415 --> 00:42:10,105
I'm nearly done with
the second volume of my novel.

606
00:42:11,305 --> 00:42:15,025
Once it sells, we'll have cash
to work with again.

607
00:42:16,945 --> 00:42:18,185
But Dad...

608
00:42:18,205 --> 00:42:19,205
That's final.

609
00:42:19,785 --> 00:42:22,465
Remember to pay that electric bill.

610
00:42:23,115 --> 00:42:25,195
The kids need their lights back on.

611
00:42:28,445 --> 00:42:29,445
Yes.

612
00:42:50,245 --> 00:42:51,345
Hmm.

613
00:43:29,245 --> 00:43:30,245
Hmm.

614
00:43:48,335 --> 00:43:51,275
"The End."

615
00:43:58,375 --> 00:43:59,375
Whew.

616
00:44:03,265 --> 00:44:05,665
Save, give me a hand.

617
00:44:06,795 --> 00:44:07,795
Yeah, Dad?

618
00:44:07,825 --> 00:44:09,985
Take Grandpa to the publisher.

619
00:44:10,385 --> 00:44:11,745
What? Right now?

620
00:44:11,945 --> 00:44:12,945
Of course.

621
00:44:15,445 --> 00:44:16,425
What?

622
00:44:16,425 --> 00:44:17,425
Gas money.

623
00:44:22,305 --> 00:44:23,305
Hmm.

624
00:44:24,945 --> 00:44:25,945
Hmm...

625
00:44:27,115 --> 00:44:28,115
Hmm.

626
00:44:28,455 --> 00:44:29,455
Uh-mmm.

627
00:44:29,505 --> 00:44:30,505
Huh?

628
00:44:32,635 --> 00:44:34,525
Hmm. That's final.

629
00:44:35,255 --> 00:44:37,985
Dad, this is a car, not a motorbike.

630
00:44:37,985 --> 00:44:41,105
Well, just drive it easy then.

631
00:44:41,505 --> 00:44:42,625
Easy how?

632
00:44:42,895 --> 00:44:44,195
Look it up online.

633
00:44:44,615 --> 00:44:47,135
Isn't that what you always say?

634
00:44:50,325 --> 00:44:51,325
Huh.

635
00:44:55,245 --> 00:44:56,605
How to save on gas.

636
00:44:57,705 --> 00:44:58,745
Sure thing.

637
00:44:58,895 --> 00:45:03,075
Here are the simple ways.
Start by driving smoothly.

638
00:45:03,075 --> 00:45:04,505
Avoid hitting the gas too hard.

639
00:45:04,665 --> 00:45:08,105
On top of that, keeping up with
regular maintenance,

640
00:45:08,105 --> 00:45:12,145
like proper tire pressure
and regular air filter changes

641
00:45:12,595 --> 00:45:14,385
can really save some gas.

642
00:45:15,825 --> 00:45:17,625
Oy...how much is that gonna save?

643
00:45:23,615 --> 00:45:24,655
Ahem.

644
00:45:26,345 --> 00:45:28,325
Well. Do you have enough cash?

645
00:45:28,765 --> 00:45:31,865
Yes, sir. Wait by the car.
I'll grab the keys first.

646
00:45:31,895 --> 00:45:32,895
Sure.

647
00:45:54,565 --> 00:45:55,565
Hmm.

648
00:45:55,915 --> 00:45:59,505
Scoot in a bit
or the sun will dry you out.

649
00:46:00,745 --> 00:46:01,745
I'll get going now.

650
00:46:11,175 --> 00:46:12,215
Hmm...

651
00:46:14,925 --> 00:46:17,105
Heh...fun, wasn't it?

652
00:46:18,305 --> 00:46:19,265
Well...

653
00:46:19,265 --> 00:46:23,585
See? I still got it.
And I hadn't written in ages.

654
00:46:23,865 --> 00:46:25,625
The craft never left me.

655
00:46:25,625 --> 00:46:26,665
Haha.

656
00:46:26,665 --> 00:46:30,545
Being a writer is in my blood.

657
00:46:31,075 --> 00:46:33,175
Cut me open,

658
00:46:33,675 --> 00:46:35,785
I bleed words.
Your father knew that.

659
00:46:37,515 --> 00:46:38,705
- Sir.
- Yes?

660
00:46:39,035 --> 00:46:40,065
Sorry to say this.

661
00:46:40,415 --> 00:46:42,745
But... Saming the Slayer, Volume 1,

662
00:46:42,775 --> 00:46:45,905
that my father published in '97,
out of kindness,

663
00:46:46,225 --> 00:46:47,245
was...

664
00:46:49,105 --> 00:46:50,105
uhm...

665
00:46:50,435 --> 00:46:53,555
Seeing you today
actually reminded me

666
00:46:53,745 --> 00:46:55,255
of unsold stock in the warehouse.

667
00:46:55,385 --> 00:46:57,985
I had someone bring it over
to donate it.

668
00:46:59,025 --> 00:47:00,815
Oh, doing some good then.

669
00:47:01,305 --> 00:47:04,185
Wonderful. I rejoice in your merit.

670
00:47:04,185 --> 00:47:05,595
Yeah. And here...

671
00:47:06,155 --> 00:47:08,905
Saming the Slayer from '97.

672
00:47:10,245 --> 00:47:11,785
Why? I don't see anything strange.

673
00:47:11,785 --> 00:47:14,545
Any novel, no matter who writes it,

674
00:47:14,565 --> 00:47:18,925
has a few copies come back unsold.
Perfectly normal.

675
00:47:18,925 --> 00:47:19,925
Hehe.

676
00:47:20,425 --> 00:47:21,425
Yes.

677
00:47:23,195 --> 00:47:24,495
Um...sir.

678
00:47:27,645 --> 00:47:30,815
Here's the thing. All of this.

679
00:47:31,465 --> 00:47:34,345
These are all yours.

680
00:47:34,585 --> 00:47:35,585
What?

681
00:47:39,095 --> 00:47:40,095
That can't be right.

682
00:47:40,355 --> 00:47:41,355
It is, sir.

683
00:47:41,415 --> 00:47:43,345
It...can't be.

684
00:47:44,505 --> 00:47:46,135
"Palang Publishing"

685
00:47:46,525 --> 00:47:47,525
"Guy: Whatchu up to?"

686
00:47:48,985 --> 00:47:50,345
"Save: An errand with Grandpa."

687
00:47:50,865 --> 00:47:51,985
"Guy: Where to after?"

688
00:47:52,935 --> 00:47:54,745
"Save: Not sure. Probably home."

689
00:47:57,825 --> 00:48:00,065
"Guy: I want to see you. Can we?"

690
00:48:09,945 --> 00:48:11,025
I understand that...

691
00:48:12,345 --> 00:48:14,865
Volume 1 may not have
hit its sales target.

692
00:48:14,865 --> 00:48:17,335
But there are people out there
asking for Volume 2.

693
00:48:18,465 --> 00:48:19,465
Who, exactly?

694
00:48:19,785 --> 00:48:20,785
Um...

695
00:48:22,315 --> 00:48:23,465
Pull up a website for me.

696
00:48:24,145 --> 00:48:27,385
Someone mentioned
a site about novels.

697
00:48:29,355 --> 00:48:30,625
There. Right there.

698
00:48:31,465 --> 00:48:33,305
Search for my pen name,
Harn Chanprai.

699
00:48:35,945 --> 00:48:36,945
Okay.

700
00:48:40,245 --> 00:48:41,245
See?

701
00:48:42,205 --> 00:48:45,385
Missing earth's scent, jungle hush,
the grip of danger in Harn's novels.

702
00:48:45,385 --> 00:48:48,665
Anyone else waiting
for Saming the Slayer Volume 2?

703
00:48:49,185 --> 00:48:53,305
Next comment. Been waiting
nearly 30 years to read it.

704
00:48:53,675 --> 00:48:56,785
No one rivals Harn Chanprai.

705
00:48:56,785 --> 00:48:59,225
I want to go back into that forest
one more time.

706
00:48:59,225 --> 00:49:01,865
I need to know if
that Saming (were-tiger)

707
00:49:03,155 --> 00:49:04,225
is truly finished.

708
00:49:07,785 --> 00:49:08,785
You see?

709
00:49:09,625 --> 00:49:11,615
I didn't want
to let these fans down.

710
00:49:11,615 --> 00:49:15,625
So I pushed myself
to finish Volume 2.

711
00:49:15,995 --> 00:49:17,985
But sir, there are only 12 comments.

712
00:49:21,365 --> 00:49:23,785
Sir, I genuinely cannot
publish this for you.

713
00:49:25,105 --> 00:49:26,585
I'm being honest with you.

714
00:49:26,585 --> 00:49:28,985
My publishing house is
barely staying afloat.

715
00:49:33,305 --> 00:49:36,645
Phuri, I need this to sell.

716
00:49:40,095 --> 00:49:41,135
I need the money.

717
00:49:43,775 --> 00:49:47,185
I'm afraid...you'll need to
write something the market wants.

718
00:49:47,745 --> 00:49:49,745
It might be worth looking into

719
00:49:49,765 --> 00:49:51,915
what people are reading these days.

720
00:49:55,505 --> 00:49:56,965
"Save: You okay?"

721
00:50:03,585 --> 00:50:05,905
"Guy: Something important
to talk to you today."

722
00:50:07,145 --> 00:50:08,225
"Save: Just say it then."

723
00:50:19,145 --> 00:50:22,145
Save, take me to a bookstore.

724
00:50:24,835 --> 00:50:26,115
Hmm. Which one?

725
00:50:26,385 --> 00:50:29,145
Whichever one people go to
these days.

726
00:50:30,575 --> 00:50:31,575
All right.

727
00:50:33,265 --> 00:50:35,825
No need. I can walk myself.

728
00:50:36,655 --> 00:50:38,265
Hmph. Show-off, huh?

729
00:50:38,655 --> 00:50:40,705
You fall and no one's gonna feel
sorry for you.

730
00:50:43,945 --> 00:50:46,945
"Save: Going to a bookstore at Siam.
Just say what you gotta say."

731
00:50:53,355 --> 00:50:56,945
"Guy: I'm at Siam too.
Come find me. Same spot."

732
00:50:57,225 --> 00:50:58,225
What's with him?

733
00:51:00,585 --> 00:51:01,585
Grandpa...

734
00:51:03,345 --> 00:51:05,145
Stay inside the store.
Don't go anywhere.

735
00:51:05,585 --> 00:51:07,385
I go see a friend. Be right back.

736
00:51:07,875 --> 00:51:08,875
Mm-hmm.

737
00:51:38,985 --> 00:51:40,185
I'm over here.

738
00:51:42,025 --> 00:51:45,425
Guy, what's on your mind?
Been holding back since yesterday.

739
00:51:46,545 --> 00:51:50,045
We're friends.
You can tell me anything.

740
00:51:51,335 --> 00:51:54,105
My Close Friends account,
you asked who's in it.

741
00:51:55,165 --> 00:51:56,585
It's only you.

742
00:51:57,705 --> 00:52:00,345
So what? Just add other people.

743
00:52:01,105 --> 00:52:03,545
No. I only want you in it.

744
00:52:07,605 --> 00:52:09,025
So cute.

745
00:52:10,375 --> 00:52:11,665
- Hey, let me see.
- Here.

746
00:52:16,565 --> 00:52:19,515
I mean I only want you
to see what I post.

747
00:52:21,605 --> 00:52:22,605
Why?

748
00:52:23,305 --> 00:52:24,425
You still don't get it?

749
00:52:24,985 --> 00:52:27,305
What is it? Just say it.

750
00:52:27,905 --> 00:52:30,145
I've been sitting on this
for a long time.

751
00:52:30,785 --> 00:52:32,665
After I say this, I don't know

752
00:52:32,945 --> 00:52:34,265
if anything will be the same.

753
00:52:35,725 --> 00:52:36,825
But...

754
00:52:59,265 --> 00:53:01,265
Save, I like you.

755
00:53:04,005 --> 00:53:05,725
"Until the Time is Right"

756
00:53:05,745 --> 00:53:06,745
Hey.

757
00:53:22,235 --> 00:53:25,345
If we can't hold on,
better sell the orphanage.

758
00:53:26,025 --> 00:53:29,105
I won't. I'm going to write
a Boys' Love novel.

759
00:53:29,585 --> 00:53:31,105
Make enough to clear the debt.

760
00:53:31,345 --> 00:53:34,025
Grandpa, you don't have to hide it.
I already know.

761
00:53:34,385 --> 00:53:38,125
You think your BL novel
will save this house?

762
00:53:38,365 --> 00:53:39,285
Of course.

763
00:53:39,305 --> 00:53:41,005
Guy, how about we give this a try?

764
00:53:42,255 --> 00:53:48,065
The world keeps
turning every day.

765
00:53:48,065 --> 00:53:53,465
And we keep
turning in its play.

766
00:53:53,465 --> 00:53:56,725
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

767
00:53:56,915 --> 00:53:59,375
We just might see
the world within.

768
00:53:59,415 --> 00:54:03,385
Let's walk together,
day by day.

769
00:54:03,555 --> 00:54:08,425
Come take the step,
what do you say?

770
00:54:14,935 --> 00:54:18,705
Let us be real,
not dreaming away,

771
00:54:18,705 --> 00:54:22,665
We'll walk in the light
of a new day.

772
00:54:22,665 --> 00:54:27,745
No one can tell
what tomorrow may say.

773
00:54:27,745 --> 00:54:30,025
Wherever the gentle wind blows,

774
00:54:30,025 --> 00:54:32,745
let our hearts flow,
soft and slow.

775
00:54:32,745 --> 00:54:37,625
And land where
our hearts both grow.

776
00:54:38,065 --> 00:54:43,905
The world keeps
turning every day.

777
00:54:43,905 --> 00:54:49,225
And we keep
turning in its play.

778
00:54:49,225 --> 00:54:52,345
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

779
00:54:52,625 --> 00:54:55,185
We just might see
the world within.

780
00:54:55,185 --> 00:54:59,305
Let's walk together,
day by day.

781
00:54:59,305 --> 00:55:04,345
Come take the step,
what do you say?

782
00:55:04,345 --> 00:55:05,345
MkvDrama.net

